The paper deals with the problem of computing approximate word-periods of a given word, which involves algorithms for pattern matching, string algorithms, and combinatorics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The problem also involves combinatorial aspects, which makes cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) another likely sub-category. The algorithmic techniques used in the paper involve graph theory and dynamic programming, which are common in cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Finally, the paper also involves probabilistic analysis and approximation algorithms, which are common in cs.LG (Machine Learning).
